# TypeScript Conventions

- Use `type` over `interface` for props and config objects
- Export all public types alongside their components
- Use `import type` for type-only imports
- Prefer `EChartsOption` from `echarts` for option typing
- Shared types go in `src/types/chart.ts`
- Shared constants go in `src/utils/theme.ts`
- React and react-dom are peer dependencies — never import them in a way that bundles them
- Keep `strict: true` — no `any` types, no implicit returns
